On Sat, 4 Jun 1994 R._Braithwaite-Lee@magic-bbs.corp.apple.com wrote:

> 
> I haven't given it a lot of thought, but I seem to recall that the knapsack
> problem and the salesperson problem are equivalent, not just in difficulty,
> but can be mapped easily. I therefore conjecture that if this is correct,
> then any secure knapsack algorithm can be converted into a secure
> salesperson problem.
> 
> If your question was posed with the idea of stimulating research into newer
> and more secure algorithms, I suspect that there is nothing exploitable
> about the salesperson problem that can't be exploited with existing
> knapsacks (most of which have been proven insecure).

	Mostly I'm curious. I've heard the salesperson problem mentioned 
as a 'hard' problem, and I wondered whether it could be done, or had been 
done. If my question produces a new and more secure algorithm, so much 
the better.
	Hurricane

